      "writtenOn": "2016-10-19T19:14:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So there’s no way to know if stuff didn’t get set up fully? That seems kind of not great. It’s pretty easy to goof and have an executable that doesn’t launch, and now we have no way to know about that.\n\n1. Let’s make the asynchronous start optional (parameterized) so that when you’re not starting Crashpad from loader-locked contexts like DllMain(), you can let it return false if things went sour.\n\n2. To be able to call this early but still allow for error reporting, provide a method that will synchronize with the thread and report the “rest of” the success/failure value that we would have seen here in synchronous mode.",
      "revId": "c7ca952ed4bfc45ef2fe428ac5badfdd04567825",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
